article.headline: Radford 69, Liberty 64
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Andre Bynum had 15 and Radford scored 15 points off turnovers to beat Liberty 69-64 in Big South Conference action Saturday night. Whit Holcomb-Faye had 12 points and Olumuyiwa Popoola added 11 for the Highlanders (9-10, 4-4). Larry Blair scored 15 and David Dees added 13 points for Liberty (7-12, 5-3). Liberty led 34-33 at half time, but shot only 29.3 percent in the second half.
